# 5. 特訓！特訓！特訓！

Kijima: In order to gain control over your smallest muscles, you have to first start paying close attention to what they're doing...
Emu: Okay!
Emu: Pay close attention... Hnng!
Kijima: Meditation can help with that. Close your eyes and focus all your attention on your nervous system.
Kijima: You'll be able to feel what your entire body is doing from your head to your toes...
Kijima: The air as it caresses your skin... Feel what your muscles underneath are doing, and learn how to control them!
Kijima: Your mind plays an important role, but your muscles are the ones doing all the work. They come first, second, third, fourth... Hundredth and foremost!
Kijima: Now, come with me! We're going to do ten laps of this park while dragging these tires around!
Nene: Oh... O-Okay...!
Kijima: Your mind and muscles need to work together in order to achieve perfect control. Next, we'll do an exercise which covers both!
Kijima: Stretch your arms out and gently squat like you're sitting down... Okay, stop there! Now stay in that position for ten minutes!
Kijima: This exercise isn't just designed to help strengthen your muscles. You have to finely control them in order to maintain the same posture. So, try to hang in there!
Emu: N-Nooo... M-My legs are starting to wobble...
Tsukasa: You can do it, Emu! Hang in there!
Kijima: Think about the role you're playing! Are you going to break character because of a little pain?
Kijima: You can do this! The muscles in your bodies are made for this!
Emu, Tsukasa, Rui & Nene: Right!
Len: L-Like this...?!
Emu: Yeah, that's perfect! Now try to stay still while keeping your arms stretched out and bottom down.
Miku: O-Oww! My legs are getting wobbly...
Len: Just a little longer...!
Emu: You guys got this! Just thirty more seconds...!
Emu: ...twenty-nine, thirty! Okay, that's it!
Len: *Sigh* That was rough!
Rin: I can't feel my legs...
Miku: And you guys have been doing stuff like this every day, Emu?
Emu: Yup! The exercise you just did is meant to help strengthen your thighs and core!
Emu: It's to make sure you can keep your posture while performing no matter what your body is doing...!
Luka: That's incredible. Can you tell us about any other exercises you've been doing?
Rui: Yes, to list a few...
Rui: We've been meditating, pulling tires around and...
Nene: Oh, this might sound a little weird, but we also did cat's cradle and even an exercise that involved learning to move our ears...
Nene: I haven't managed to yet, but anyone apparently can given enough practice...
Tsukasa: Strength training and conditioning are both important, but the primary goal of these exercises is to achieve perfect control of our bodies.
Tsukasa: We've mostly been learning how to control every muscle right down to our fingertips, including ones we don't think about normally.
Len: Really?! That sounds challenging, but also fun...! Can you tell us more about what you guys have been doing later?
Nene: Sure.
MEIKO: It's nice to hear that you're already learning so much from this other troupe.
MEIKO: And they sound very different from Shunmeiza, so I'm sure you all stand to gain quite a lot from working with them!
Len: Especially you, Emu. You seem really pumped up today for some reason!
Luka: Oh, is it because you were chosen to play the lead?
Emu: Yup! Also...
Emu: I absolutely want this play to succeed so that we get to be a part of Mikazukigumi's next production!
Emu: Since working with lots and lots of people on lots and lots of different things seems like the best way for us to learn!
Tsukasa: Yes, I agree...
Tsukasa: Even when we were working with Shunmeiza, working with proven talent helped us make quite a few new discoveries.
Nene: Yeah, from Seiryuin to Asahi and Bakuno... Getting to perform alongside such talented people has already helped us learn a lot.
Rui: Yes, and... Performing on a real stage is simply the best way to gain experience.
Rui: So, in order to make our dreams come true, let's make our play about Ushiwakamaru a good one.
Emu: Yeah!
Emu: Alright, let's all do some of those exercises again together!
Emu: Starting from the top of the Kijima Special! Sprinting at full speed! Let's go!
Len: Emu, wait! I wanna run with you!
Tsukasa: We should join her as well! Not so fast, Emu!
Luka: Oh, everyone's so full of energy today.
MEIKO: I love how motivated they are! Let's all run with them, shall we?!
